WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.321
Praised Jesus and Mary, nice greetings to everyone watching our you tube channel.

00:00:04.321 --> 00:00:08.005
And in the the beginning I want to ask all of you to subscribe to our you tube channel if you have not already.

00:00:08.005 --> 00:00:12.302
I forgot to say that up until now, but I have remembered to do it now.

00:00:13.520 --> 00:00:17.019
With me today here is special guest, one young man.

00:00:18.000 --> 00:00:22.600
As they say a lot of people that get rich and famous.

00:00:22.600 --> 00:00:25.520
Usually separate them selfs from God.

00:00:25.520 --> 00:00:30.520
However my guest today, has achieved fame, success and money.

00:00:30.520 --> 00:00:37.134
But exactly that has encouraged him to grow closer to God.

00:00:37.134 --> 00:00:41.694
At the beginning of the video, I greet our Luku Perkovića.

00:00:41.694 --> 00:00:44.370
Famous video game player.

00:00:44.370 --> 00:00:47.260
So here Luka, in the beginning of our video.

00:00:47.260 --> 00:00:49.472
Maybe is the best that you introduce yourself.

00:00:49.472 --> 00:00:53.740
We know that you are 21 year old young man from Zagreb.

00:00:53.740 --> 00:00:57.153
And everyone knows that you are famous video games player.

00:00:57.153 --> 00:00:58.975
I have 22 years now.

00:00:58.975 --> 00:01:00.100
22 then now.

00:01:00.100 --> 00:01:03.425
Yes I'm pretty sure about that, even tho I would like to have 21.

00:01:03.425 --> 00:01:07.280
But I'm soon celebrating 23, years are flying by.

00:01:10.280 --> 00:01:13.282
I am Luka Perković, 

00:01:13.282 --> 00:01:17.768
I was born in Zagreb and grew up in Rakov Potok. 

00:01:17.768 --> 00:01:22.014
A little village near Samobor.

00:01:23.000 --> 00:01:27.851
I was living there for almost 17 years, 16 to be exact.

00:01:28.840 --> 00:01:33.854
Then I moved to Berlin to follow my new path in life.

00:01:33.854 --> 00:01:38.733
There I have started my professional career playing League of Legends.

00:01:38.733 --> 00:01:43.971
So Luka, please tell us, how they say in media, 

00:01:43.971 --> 00:01:47.916
That you make millions without breaking the sweat.

00:01:47.916 --> 00:01:51.240
I still think that's not easy because playing video games and winning tournaments.

00:01:51.240 --> 00:01:54.720
Must be very demanding and stressful.

00:01:54.733 --> 00:01:57.240
And in the start I would like to hear exactly that.

00:01:57.240 --> 00:02:00.893
How hard is playing video games and tournaments like that?

00:02:00.893 --> 00:02:04.512
What is that you have to do to get some victory and profit?

00:02:04.512 --> 00:02:08.919
What does your average day of preparation for such tournaments look like?

00:02:11.880 --> 00:02:15.694
It is a process that started many years ago.

00:02:15.694 --> 00:02:19.611
I think 10 years to be exact.

00:02:23.600 --> 00:02:28.344
I started playing amateur in 2014/2015 when I was in high school.

00:02:28.344 --> 00:02:32.686
I discovered that I had a talent for it.

00:02:32.686 --> 00:02:35.451
I was very high in the player rankings.

00:02:35.451 --> 00:02:37.994
Then I started joining amateur teams.

00:02:37.994 --> 00:02:40.986
And with one amateur team I qualified for the professional league.

00:02:40.986 --> 00:02:43.480
It was all completely new.

00:02:45.495 --> 00:02:48.570
Something new both for me and for us Croats.

00:02:52.560 --> 00:02:56.579
In the beginning, I practiced 12 hours a day.

00:02:56.579 --> 00:02:58.866
Literally all day.

00:02:58.866 --> 00:03:01.139
It went on for years.

00:03:01.139 --> 00:03:06.590
Since we are a successful team every year.

00:03:06.590 --> 00:03:10.315
Our season lasts from January to October.

00:03:10.315 --> 00:03:12.315
Sometimes November.

00:03:12.315 --> 00:03:16.280
It depends on how successful we are in the last tournament.    

00:03:18.280 --> 00:03:21.009
All of that is very exhausting.

00:03:21.009 --> 00:03:26.120
But the hardest part is working with  your teammates.

00:03:26.120 --> 00:03:28.911
Interpersonal relationships

00:03:28.911 --> 00:03:32.066
Yes, that might be a good thing to say to those who will watch the video.

00:03:32.066 --> 00:03:34.311
And are not into video games.

00:03:34.311 --> 00:03:36.962
What I have read is

00:03:36.962 --> 00:03:39.334
You play in a team of 5 people and attack?

00:03:41.320 --> 00:03:45.853
Yes, we have our "tower" and the goal is to destroy the opponent's "tower".

00:03:49.840 --> 00:03:53.000
Let's say the game is a mixture of modern chess 

00:03:53.000 --> 00:03:56.320
And the rest is mechanics, typing and reaction speed.

00:03:56.320 --> 00:03:58.848
Also lots of calculations.

00:03:58.848 --> 00:04:03.361
You generally need to be fast with your fingers.

00:04:03.361 --> 00:04:07.520
You have played in Europe and now you play in America, right?

00:04:07.520 --> 00:04:10.400
Yes, I played in Europe.

00:04:10.400 --> 00:04:13.480
I competed there for 5 years.

00:04:15.480 --> 00:04:18.012
How much did your transfer cost?

00:04:19.164 --> 00:04:22.844
I don't know exactly how much it cost.

00:04:22.844 --> 00:04:25.120
I want to hear it first hand, if media is right.

00:04:25.120 --> 00:04:27.580
 A couple million dollars.

00:04:29.560 --> 00:04:32.790
My first salary was a hundred dollars a month.

00:04:32.790 --> 00:04:37.905
So this industry has grown a lot over the years.

00:04:37.905 --> 00:04:42.405
Of course, that's why there are more and more people who are interested in it.

00:04:44.400 --> 00:04:49.337
There are a lot of them in Europe, but it is also very popular in China and Korea.

00:04:50.320 --> 00:04:54.377
For example, I am more famous in China and Korea than here in Croatia.

00:04:54.377 --> 00:04:57.364
Which is really incredible.

00:04:57.364 --> 00:05:05.310
What I also read is that you are the eighteenth highest paid player in World and the third in Europe.

00:05:05.310 --> 00:05:07.742
Is that true?

00:05:07.742 --> 00:05:09.422
I do not know that.

00:05:09.422 --> 00:05:13.280
When someone tells me something they read on the Internet, I simply don't know if it's actually true.

00:05:15.280 --> 00:05:20.793
What is written on the internet is not always true, so you really wouldn't know.

00:05:23.760 --> 00:05:30.928
What interests me is, we started talking about what your working day looks like.

00:05:30.928 --> 00:05:37.139
Many young people today play games, many as a hobby, but many also become addicted.

00:05:37.139 --> 00:05:40.757
How dangerous is it to play video games anyway?

00:05:40.757 --> 00:05:46.955
How much do you, as a person whose job it is, see that it affects you negatively?

00:05:46.955 --> 00:05:52.532
That is, to all young people who become addicted to it, who play for hours and hours?

00:05:55.520 --> 00:06:00.045
So, first of all, we currently have the best infrastructure.

00:06:00.045 --> 00:06:04.840
We get up at 9 in the morning

00:06:04.840 --> 00:06:08.080
And at 9.30 we have physical exercises before our training.

00:06:08.080 --> 00:06:11.906
It lasts for an hour, after which we have a break.

00:06:11.906 --> 00:06:15.597
During the vacation, we take a shower, have lunch, and relax.

00:06:15.597 --> 00:06:18.360
After that we have a meeting.

00:06:18.360 --> 00:06:23.000
We talk about what is our problem is, what do we need to change.

00:06:23.000 --> 00:06:26.547
Every two weeks, new "bakes" arrive in the game.

00:06:26.547 --> 00:06:28.766
The game changes every two weeks.

00:06:28.766 --> 00:06:31.920
Sometimes little by little, but sometimes a lot.

00:06:31.920 --> 00:06:35.346
So it is constant learning and discovering something new.

00:06:35.346 --> 00:06:40.520
It's the hardest part of the game, nothing is ever the same, it changes all the time.

00:06:40.520 --> 00:06:43.800
And that's why teams go up and down.

00:06:43.800 --> 00:06:48.598
 They can't keep up with it.

00:06:50.560 --> 00:06:53.696
After the meeting, we play together as a team for 5 hours.

00:06:55.680 --> 00:06:58.480
We also have video analysis of the game.

00:06:58.480 --> 00:07:02.369
Where we talk for twenty, thirty minutes about what to change.

00:07:02.369 --> 00:07:04.376
We have debreef at the end of the day.

00:07:04.376 --> 00:07:08.820
And then sometimes, since we struggled this summer.

00:07:08.820 --> 00:07:12.471
We had one extra block at night, two-three more hours.

00:07:12.471 --> 00:07:16.621
So our day used to start at 9 in the morning and end at 9 in the evening.

00:07:16.621 --> 00:07:19.604
Those days are really tiring.

00:07:21.600 --> 00:07:24.645
This year we had official matches 3 days a week.

00:07:24.645 --> 00:07:27.146
Which are broadcast for the audience.

00:07:27.146 --> 00:07:30.581
Those days are a little easier but more stressful in a different way.

00:07:33.560 --> 00:07:38.360
Adrenaline hits you, you're tired after a match because you always want to do your best.

00:07:39.360 --> 00:07:42.595
The structure is a little different on those days.

00:07:42.595 --> 00:07:45.000
But there is still a lot of things to do.

00:07:45.000 --> 00:07:49.040
We have one day a week off and that day we don't do anything. 

00:07:49.040 --> 00:07:53.556
We need to rest and mentally prepare for the next week.

00:07:55.520 --> 00:08:00.736
Sounds like a very tight schedule, I'm curious what you do on that day off.

00:08:03.720 --> 00:08:06.081
It depends on how tired I am.

00:08:13.080 --> 00:08:16.407
Sometimes we have some activities.

00:08:16.407 --> 00:08:20.174
And sometimes I stay at home, do nothing all day, take a day to rest.

00:08:25.160 --> 00:08:29.662
I feel lazy then, but that day comes in handy to recharge my energy for the next day.

00:08:29.662 --> 00:08:33.079
Sometimes we go hiking.

00:08:33.079 --> 00:08:37.261
Once we even went to the beach.

00:08:37.261 --> 00:08:40.026
Just trying to do something different.

00:08:40.026 --> 00:08:44.145
Once, when we were really struggling, I stayed to play for 10 hours on that off day.

00:08:44.145 --> 00:08:46.760
So that I can practice something new

00:08:46.760 --> 00:08:48.880
And bring it into the next week of preparation.

00:08:48.880 --> 00:08:53.865
It all depends on how I feel and what we need.

00:08:53.865 --> 00:09:01.917
When you started doing well with the games, when you're on that upward trajectory.

00:09:01.917 --> 00:09:04.121
Were you tempted to get arrogant?

00:09:05.120 --> 00:09:07.697
Ugh, yes, of course.

00:09:13.680 --> 00:09:17.744
Of course it was there from the beginning, when I started winning.

00:09:17.744 --> 00:09:19.927
As soon as I entered the professional league.

00:09:19.927 --> 00:09:23.619
 I immediately won the title.

00:09:23.619 --> 00:09:26.800
It used to be called "lcs".

00:09:27.800 --> 00:09:31.485
And of course that immediately  struck me.

00:09:33.480 --> 00:09:35.221
That summer we won another title.

00:09:35.221 --> 00:09:39.364
But then we played badly in the world championship and we failed completely.

00:09:39.364 --> 00:09:42.315
Basically, people hated me a lot on the internet back then.

00:09:44.280 --> 00:09:48.600
Thousands of people sent me death threats.

00:09:52.600 --> 00:09:54.088
They didn't like me one bit.

00:09:54.088 --> 00:09:58.256
Spring after that, we are great again.

00:09:58.256 --> 00:10:01.661
We also played well on international tournament.

00:10:01.661 --> 00:10:04.717
Fans started to like me again.

00:10:06.680 --> 00:10:10.200
It's like an amusement park, your ego and emotions are constantly going up and down.

00:10:15.200 --> 00:10:18.708
Basically after that part, my career was going in positive direction.

00:10:22.680 --> 00:10:26.680
In the 2019 season, we had the best season of all teams ever.

00:10:29.680 --> 00:10:32.473
We lost only one full match all season.

00:10:32.473 --> 00:10:34.473
And that was in the world championship  final.

00:10:35.440 --> 00:10:38.499
That year, my ego was extremely  big.

00:10:40.480 --> 00:10:42.472
I had changed my playing position then.

00:10:42.472 --> 00:10:44.902
From one position to another.

00:10:44.902 --> 00:10:49.626
In that second position, I was world class in just a few months of practice.

00:10:53.600 --> 00:10:55.280
Which of course raised my ego to a new level.

00:10:56.280 --> 00:10:59.760
So I struggled with that a lot.

00:11:01.760 --> 00:11:05.360
But at the same time, to associate it with the spiritual part now.

00:11:07.360 --> 00:11:10.600
I was raised in the faith, but it was never deep in it.

00:11:10.600 --> 00:11:13.600
Let's say it, I was just a traditional believer.

00:11:13.600 --> 00:11:18.313
But I didn't know about anything else.

00:11:18.313 --> 00:11:20.313
We can maybe talk about it later.

00:11:20.313 --> 00:11:22.720
We can do it now since you have started the topic.

00:11:22.720 --> 00:11:25.360
So how did your deeper relationship with religion begin?

00:11:25.360 --> 00:11:28.890
And in all that, in the world you are in, how do you even find time for God?

00:11:28.890 --> 00:11:32.982
Today, the whole world is busy and many young people say that there is no time for God.

00:11:32.982 --> 00:11:35.129
And that is the devil's greatest victory.

00:11:35.129 --> 00:11:40.326
Convince today's man, occupy him so much that he has no time for God.

00:11:40.326 --> 00:11:42.926
How do you manage that?

00:11:42.926 --> 00:11:46.050
How did your journey to a deeper relationship with God begin?

00:11:46.050 --> 00:11:53.861
Just like you said, there is so many distractions,  cell phones,  ipods, televisions, computers and screens.

00:11:53.861 --> 00:12:00.483
I personally find that I rarely actually have a break from it all during the day.

00:12:00.483 --> 00:12:04.254
50 years ago there was no information about anything at all.

00:12:04.254 --> 00:12:06.014
Now there is information all around us.

00:12:06.014 --> 00:12:10.565
So much information that in the end you no longer know what is true and what is a lie.

00:12:10.565 --> 00:12:12.120
What is real and what isn't.

00:12:15.120 --> 00:12:17.180
Then it preoccupies you, creates problems.

00:12:17.180 --> 00:12:20.423
At the end, when you want to relax, do something else.

00:12:20.423 --> 00:12:23.840
You can't because your brain is boiling, it can't process so much information.

00:12:27.120 --> 00:12:29.800
It simply can not handle all of the information that you read everyday .

00:12:33.139 --> 00:12:34.699
Along with my job.....

00:12:45.680 --> 00:12:48.680
In the first three years, actually four, of my professional life.

00:12:53.680 --> 00:12:55.359
Every year I wanted something more.

00:12:55.359 --> 00:12:57.299
Some new challenges.

00:12:57.299 --> 00:12:59.040
I wanted to achieve something more.

00:12:59.040 --> 00:13:01.320
I wanted to be better.

00:13:01.320 --> 00:13:04.884
I wanted to be more famous, earn more money, etc.

00:13:05.880 --> 00:13:09.939
Typical human desires for something higher and better all the time.

00:13:12.920 --> 00:13:14.729
So I just kept going.

00:13:16.720 --> 00:13:19.002
I need to add that in that time.

00:13:19.002 --> 00:13:22.828
 I really started to separate myself from God

00:13:22.828 --> 00:13:25.462
Although I still went to mass.

00:13:25.462 --> 00:13:28.264
Actually my separation from God started even earlier than that.

00:13:28.264 --> 00:13:31.040
It started in high school, when I entered that adolescent phase.

00:13:35.040 --> 00:13:40.462
I started to form my own opinions about the world and life.

00:13:41.440 --> 00:13:44.821
I had my phases that I don't know how to describe.

00:13:47.800 --> 00:13:49.477
I believed that God exists.

00:13:50.440 --> 00:13:52.108
 Someone had to make the world.

00:13:52.108 --> 00:13:56.390
The world could not have been created by the snapping of fingers or the big bang theory.

00:13:56.390 --> 00:13:59.680
God had to make the world and man.

00:13:59.680 --> 00:14:01.400
And after that.

00:14:02.400 --> 00:14:06.423
What God had to, was able to and wanted to do I didn't know.

00:14:06.423 --> 00:14:09.633
I also had my theories that evil and satan does not exist.

00:14:12.600 --> 00:14:15.075
But we all decide for ourselves what we want.

00:14:15.075 --> 00:14:16.879
Whether we will be a good people or not.

00:14:16.879 --> 00:14:18.862
I've become something of an atheist, let's say.

00:14:18.862 --> 00:14:22.624
Although I don't know if atheists believe that god exists or not.

00:14:25.600 --> 00:14:28.349
I think not, but let's not talk now about what I know and don't know.

00:14:29.320 --> 00:14:32.937
But I had my own idea about life and everything.

00:14:33.920 --> 00:14:35.601
All of it kinda started to hit me in the head.

00:14:42.600 --> 00:14:45.200
At that time I also started taking drugs.

00:14:45.200 --> 00:14:47.827
At that time I also started taking drugs.

00:14:49.800 --> 00:14:53.983
And in those moments when I would smoke, thoughts would come to my head.

00:14:53.983 --> 00:14:56.033
"What are you doing? Are you stupid?"

00:14:56.033 --> 00:15:00.238
After a while I stopped and now I haven't smoked weed in years.

00:15:00.238 --> 00:15:05.506
Do you know what is youth's favorite sentence in the Holy Scriptures?

00:15:05.506 --> 00:15:07.480
What is?

00:15:07.480 --> 00:15:12.235
When Jesus was with his disciples on the mountain.

00:15:12.235 --> 00:15:15.369
And then he told them, as the evangelist describes.

00:15:15.369 --> 00:15:17.334
".. and there was a lot of grass.."

00:15:19.320 --> 00:15:21.760
This is just a joke.

00:15:24.760 --> 00:15:27.283
Under no circumstances does Stjepan recommend that you consume drugs.

00:15:32.280 --> 00:15:35.288
Mostly, I will skip some parts now.

00:15:37.280 --> 00:15:40.181
But there was one moment before the world final when I couldn't sleep.

00:15:40.181 --> 00:15:42.572
That was in a period where we had a lot of success.

00:15:46.560 --> 00:15:50.478
My atheism was at an all-time high then.

00:15:53.440 --> 00:15:56.270
But that evening before the world final

00:15:56.270 --> 00:15:59.607
 I played a song on my cell phone.

00:15:59.607 --> 00:16:02.720
"Fear not for I am with you."

00:16:02.720 --> 00:16:05.495
It gave me, my heart, peace.

00:16:05.495 --> 00:16:08.899
I fell asleep and was ready for tomorrow.

00:16:08.899 --> 00:16:13.488
We lost zero-three but well, at least I slept.

00:16:13.488 --> 00:16:18.780
This is not a story where we won in the end, but that's okay.

00:16:20.760 --> 00:16:26.115
During those years, I filled myself with false beliefs

00:16:26.115 --> 00:16:28.694
Some kind of false ideology.

00:16:29.680 --> 00:16:33.400
And I really did thought.

00:16:35.420 --> 00:16:36.444
I thought that I

00:16:36.444 --> 00:16:40.412
That you create your own good, your own evil, it all depends on how hard you try.

00:16:40.412 --> 00:16:42.932
The more you give, the more you will have.

00:16:42.932 --> 00:16:48.280
Of course there were some good things looking at it that way, but there were far more negative ones.

00:16:48.280 --> 00:16:50.985
That rotted my brain.

00:16:53.960 --> 00:16:57.924
At the end of that year, I was exhausted both mentally and physically.

00:16:57.924 --> 00:17:02.116
I carried a lot of childhood trauma with me.

00:17:02.116 --> 00:17:05.643
Which I have burr inside me.

00:17:05.643 --> 00:17:09.599
When I returned home to my family house, I could not sleep.

00:17:13.560 --> 00:17:16.040
It was very difficult for me.

00:17:17.040 --> 00:17:20.997
So I Went to sleep at my brothers place.

00:17:21.960 --> 00:17:26.240
That night I was not well, I was vomiting and my brother prayed over me.

00:17:30.240 --> 00:17:33.480
And in those days, I have had enough of everything.

00:17:35.480 --> 00:17:37.200
Literally everything.

00:17:39.200 --> 00:17:41.852
That was a psychological and spiritual bottom for me.

00:17:44.840 --> 00:17:50.880
One evening, very tempting thoughts came to me.

00:17:55.880 --> 00:18:01.141
And then, that evening, I gave up everything.

00:18:01.141 --> 00:18:04.927
All the weed and drugs that I used.

00:18:09.920 --> 00:18:12.001
I mean, I've never been and I don't want to sound like an addict.

00:18:12.001 --> 00:18:14.847
I was curious and tried it all out of curiosity.

00:18:14.847 --> 00:18:16.480
But when curiosity takes you somewhere...

00:18:16.480 --> 00:18:18.768
That's where everyone starts!

00:18:21.998 --> 00:18:24.511
I regretted everything I took and everything I have tried.

00:18:24.511 --> 00:18:27.654
I said I would never do it again and I have not used drugs since then.

00:18:29.192 --> 00:18:32.266
After all of that, just to clarify that this wasn't an over-night decision.

00:18:32.266 --> 00:18:35.856
After that I started my conversion.

00:18:35.856 --> 00:18:37.876
I went to confession, to mass.

00:18:37.876 --> 00:18:42.178
I started learning about religion, my brother helped me with that.

00:18:44.160 --> 00:18:48.920
He taught me what mass is and why I go to mass and its parts.

00:18:49.920 --> 00:18:54.440
I started reading spiritual books and studying the Bible.

00:18:56.440 --> 00:18:58.240
Slowly got back into faith.

00:19:00.240 --> 00:19:02.834
I also went to hagiotheraphy therapy.

00:19:03.800 --> 00:19:05.762
Went there couple of times.

00:19:08.559 --> 00:19:10.919
It helped me a lot, I learned a lot of useful information.

00:19:15.880 --> 00:19:18.581
And that's how my faith actually began.

00:19:18.581 --> 00:19:22.997
Because even though I was in the faith before, raised in the faith and ministered in the church.

00:19:22.997 --> 00:19:25.321
I didn't really know anything about religion.

00:19:25.321 --> 00:19:29.088
I couldn't wait for the priest until the  end of the mass to give me 10 kunas for ice cream, when I was a child. 

00:19:42.080 --> 00:19:45.938
Oh, yes, in addition to all that,  when I was struggling  mentally.

00:19:45.938 --> 00:19:47.958
My dad got cancer.

00:19:47.958 --> 00:19:51.520
He has beat it once before; but it came back.

00:19:53.520 --> 00:19:55.716
That was before my breakdown.

00:19:57.680 --> 00:20:00.120
But it has all added up.

00:20:01.120 --> 00:20:07.398
Even the first time when he got cancer, I cried because of the thought that one day he will be gone.

00:20:07.398 --> 00:20:09.219
I had some unsolved problems.

00:20:12.200 --> 00:20:15.520
All this accumulated and I decided to come back home.

00:20:15.520 --> 00:20:20.816
God restored me little by little, more and more.

00:20:27.800 --> 00:20:29.432
So, my dad got cancer again

00:20:31.400 --> 00:20:33.469
And that got to his had a little bit.

00:20:36.440 --> 00:20:38.348
It affected me a lot.

00:20:41.320 --> 00:20:44.443
After a few months, in the spring of 2020.

00:20:44.443 --> 00:20:49.661
We won everything again for spring.

00:20:49.661 --> 00:20:54.847
Due to corona, the tournament, which is normally in May, was cancelled.

00:20:54.847 --> 00:20:58.357
I returned back home.

00:20:58.357 --> 00:21:01.633
Dad was very sick from the cancer at that time.

00:21:01.633 --> 00:21:04.563
He was on a lot of drugs.

00:21:04.563 --> 00:21:08.160
He become slightly different person.

00:21:08.160 --> 00:21:11.458
When a disease takes a person, it really changes them.

00:21:11.458 --> 00:21:15.978
That was very hard for me and I struggled with faith again.

00:21:15.978 --> 00:21:20.750
I would literally go to forest to cry.

00:21:20.750 --> 00:21:23.033
To Scream!

00:21:23.033 --> 00:21:25.564
Why this? Why that?

00:21:25.564 --> 00:21:31.702
At least God gave me good conversation with my father a few months before all of this.

00:21:31.702 --> 00:21:34.559
You had your chance.

00:21:34.559 --> 00:21:37.213
Yes, we had the opportunity to solve a lot of things.

00:21:37.213 --> 00:21:42.863
Let's just say that at that time I was at peace in my heart about my problems.

00:21:44.840 --> 00:21:50.652
But I still couldn't come to terms with the fact that he might not be there.

00:21:50.652 --> 00:21:53.733
And that might happen soon.

00:21:53.733 --> 00:21:56.200
That was just one more

00:21:56.200 --> 00:21:58.873
how it's called,

00:22:00.840 --> 00:22:03.393
one more step, on my way to faith!

00:22:07.360 --> 00:22:10.451
So it actually strengthened my faith even more.

00:22:12.440 --> 00:22:14.793
And last year.

00:22:14.793 --> 00:22:17.743
Was it actually last year?

00:22:17.743 --> 00:22:19.880
Yes, last year, about 10 months ago.

00:22:19.880 --> 00:22:24.934
I went to silence for 3 days.

00:22:24.934 --> 00:22:27.462
After silence, I would go back home to eat dinner and sleep.

00:22:27.462 --> 00:22:31.440
The next day I would go back.

00:22:31.440 --> 00:22:35.524
After that I enrolled in spiritual silence online.

00:22:35.524 --> 00:22:40.855
So I followed my considerations every day for 3 months.

00:22:42.840 --> 00:22:45.245
There many new things opened up for me.

00:22:49.240 --> 00:22:52.383
So I would say that I am just at the beginning of my spiritual journey.

00:22:54.360 --> 00:22:57.720
I still have a lot of things to learn.

00:22:58.720 --> 00:23:00.240
But I'm already much better.

00:23:02.240 --> 00:23:04.960
I see changes in myself, in my behavior.

00:23:06.960 --> 00:23:09.528
Sometimes it feels like I'm out of my body.

00:23:09.528 --> 00:23:12.261
It's like I'm in a third perspective.

00:23:12.261 --> 00:23:16.700
I see myself, how I would react two years ago and how I react now.

00:23:16.700 --> 00:23:20.874
Although I still get angry, react, argue and what not.

00:23:20.874 --> 00:23:23.894
But you reconcile.

00:23:23.894 --> 00:23:25.936
Yes, I make peace.

00:23:25.936 --> 00:23:29.613
I feel a little less that I need to be in control.

00:23:29.613 --> 00:23:33.040
That I need to know everything.

00:23:33.040 --> 00:23:37.651
Now you leave it to God.

00:23:37.651 --> 00:23:40.424
That's right, I trust him.

00:23:40.424 --> 00:23:45.581
I realize that faith is the most important part of my life.

00:23:45.581 --> 00:23:47.143
I believe that everything will be fine.

00:23:47.143 --> 00:23:54.064
I believe that whatever problems I have, will be solved.

00:23:54.064 --> 00:24:00.588
Also I have felt that my problems have not disappeared in those 12 months.

00:24:00.588 --> 00:24:05.398
From the loss of the world final, that hit me really hard.

00:24:05.398 --> 00:24:07.458
To the situation at home

00:24:07.458 --> 00:24:09.945
First dad's illness, then dad's death.

00:24:13.920 --> 00:24:17.326
In the end, I broke up with my club, which I had been with for 6 years.

00:24:17.326 --> 00:24:20.713
I was with them from the beginning.

00:24:20.713 --> 00:24:25.778
We raised the club from an amateur to a professional league.

00:24:25.778 --> 00:24:30.018
From nobody we became the most famous in the world.

00:24:32.000 --> 00:24:34.214
That breakup hit me really hard.

00:24:34.214 --> 00:24:38.077
Although, looking back on it now.

00:24:38.077 --> 00:24:41.683
And listening to stories from people who are now in that club.

00:24:43.128 --> 00:24:47.345
Everything makes sense to me now.

00:24:48.771 --> 00:24:51.944
I'm glad everything turned out the way it did.

00:24:51.944 --> 00:24:55.912
Although of course it was very difficult for me at that moment.

00:24:57.880 --> 00:25:01.074
It was all very stressful , I haven't slept in days.

00:25:03.040 --> 00:25:05.756
It was very tiring for me.

00:25:05.756 --> 00:25:11.057
But with the support of family and friends, everything is easier.

00:25:11.057 --> 00:25:15.524
God helped me to come to terms with the situation.

00:25:18.935 --> 00:25:22.600
So now I'm here.

00:25:22.600 --> 00:25:25.148
God sent me here.

00:25:27.120 --> 00:25:31.446
When we met on Instagram, I first looked at who this guy was.

00:25:31.446 --> 00:25:33.232
He plays video games.

00:25:33.232 --> 00:25:36.296
So I said, my God, are there believers even in that world.

00:25:36.296 --> 00:25:38.866
What did you think when you saw me?

00:25:38.866 --> 00:25:42.000
I was shocked when I sow priest on Instagram.

00:25:42.000 --> 00:25:43.616
Where has this world gone?

00:25:47.600 --> 00:25:53.276
Luka, thank you from the bottom of my heart for this testimony of faith and everything else.

00:25:53.276 --> 00:25:59.124
Finally, for conclusion, what would you really recommend to young people who are into the game world?

00:25:59.124 --> 00:26:01.362
Who are all young like you.

00:26:01.362 --> 00:26:03.787
Do you have a message for them?

00:26:03.787 --> 00:26:06.001
What would you say to all of them?

00:26:06.001 --> 00:26:08.956
That maybe they don't repeat those things that you yourself went through.

00:26:08.956 --> 00:26:11.151
Thank God your story is positive.

00:26:11.151 --> 00:26:16.824
You found God, you didn't allow yourself to be carried away by pride, fame nor money.

00:26:18.800 --> 00:26:21.450
And least at first, you seem like a normal person.

00:26:21.450 --> 00:26:22.890
Thank you!

00:26:25.880 --> 00:26:29.234
I have a few thoughts for parents and their children.

00:26:32.200 --> 00:26:37.029
First, for parents, if someone plays games, it does not immediately mean that they are addicted.

00:26:37.029 --> 00:26:40.993
That it is very bad for them and that they will not achieve anything in life.

00:26:40.993 --> 00:26:45.277
I learned a lot about life from video games.

00:26:46.865 --> 00:26:48.957
How to treat things in life better.

00:26:50.920 --> 00:26:53.345
You can find something positive everything, it depends on how you look at it.

00:26:53.345 --> 00:26:55.521
Of course, children should be controlled.

00:26:55.521 --> 00:26:58.893
So that it does not turn into an addiction.

00:27:02.880 --> 00:27:05.205
Or that it becomes the only thing in their lifes that makes sense.

00:27:07.200 --> 00:27:11.976
Second thing would be "Drugs are not the answer, nor the solution"

00:27:12.960 --> 00:27:15.664
And if you are in friend group,

00:27:18.640 --> 00:27:20.535
in which they force you to do something.

00:27:22.520 --> 00:27:25.381
It's best that you leave those friend and go to church on Sveti Duh.

00:27:25.381 --> 00:27:27.381
They have community gatherings on Thursday.

00:27:29.360 --> 00:27:31.499
That will surely be better for you!

00:27:35.043 --> 00:27:38.401
Likewise, of course,
It is better to set a time and whatever you do it good.

00:27:38.401 --> 00:27:43.087
Maybe you will need to study 12 hours a day for the exams.

00:27:43.087 --> 00:27:47.500
But spending quality time is better than spending too much time on something.

00:27:49.638 --> 00:27:54.654
There were many times when I spent 12 hours a day playing games.

00:27:54.654 --> 00:27:59.654
I would have been much better if I had rested a bit.

00:27:59.654 --> 00:28:05.783
Analyze a little, rest, take a walk.

00:28:08.760 --> 00:28:12.299
Live healthier and move a lot more.

00:28:12.299 --> 00:28:17.434
Because that way you will learn more and improve yourself.

00:28:17.434 --> 00:28:21.873
Whatever you do, do it well and do not waste time.

00:28:28.840 --> 00:28:29.420
And yes.

00:28:29.420 --> 00:28:32.273
Everyone is destined for something in life!

00:28:35.240 --> 00:28:40.326
Don't think that everyone is for playing video gamers, for sports, for this or that.

00:28:40.326 --> 00:28:42.320
Or for being friars.

00:28:42.320 --> 00:28:44.264
Yes, of course, hardly anyone.

00:28:44.264 --> 00:28:46.305
But there are people for that too!

00:28:50.280 --> 00:28:52.226
For example, my knee is really messed up.

00:28:52.226 --> 00:28:55.905
I can't kneel or jump, it all hurts a lot.

00:28:57.880 --> 00:29:01.456
I tried to play sports when I was little.

00:29:01.456 --> 00:29:03.780
But God was sending me in a different way.

00:29:06.760 --> 00:29:10.272
So sports are not for everyone, nor are video games.

00:29:10.272 --> 00:29:14.653
Or anything else, don't push yourself too hard.

00:29:14.653 --> 00:29:17.823
And finally, tell us what your plans are for the future.

00:29:17.823 --> 00:29:20.781
Can we expect you in Croatia, are you coming back?

00:29:20.781 --> 00:29:24.917
Where will you be in the next period of your life?

00:29:24.917 --> 00:29:28.352
I learned not to plan too much for my future.

00:29:28.352 --> 00:29:33.205
Often when I plan something, it doesn't happen according to my plans.

00:29:33.205 --> 00:29:37.276
I always have some ideas, I think of something new.

00:29:39.240 --> 00:29:43.092
But I will live in Croatia when I finish my career.

00:29:43.092 --> 00:29:46.666
That's something I've already decided.

00:29:46.666 --> 00:29:50.596
I'm not staying in Los Angeles or anywhere else.

00:29:50.596 --> 00:29:55.484
I love being at home and I love my country.

00:29:55.484 --> 00:29:58.256
I plan to live here.

00:29:58.256 --> 00:30:03.104
When, how and what I don't know yet.

00:30:03.104 --> 00:30:06.868
Because I don't know for how long I will compete.

00:30:06.868 --> 00:30:10.299
But I will stay in the industry after my retirement.

00:30:10.299 --> 00:30:16.812
One last sentence for the end, you have probably heard in the church already but you also know what I do.

00:30:16.812 --> 00:30:20.994
What do you think about The new evangelization?

00:30:20.994 --> 00:30:22.994
How can we evangalize today?

00:30:30.960 --> 00:30:34.572
That something I have started learning about when  I was angry, stressed end frustrated.

00:30:39.560 --> 00:30:42.724
There was so many moments in my life where I wanted to change something on someone.

00:30:43.324 --> 00:30:45.320
I didn't like this or that about them.

00:30:45.996 --> 00:30:48.396
Then I realized that there were a lot of things I did not like about me.

00:30:49.848 --> 00:30:53.048
Now I first look at me and then I look for love.

00:30:54.040 --> 00:30:58.136
First love for yourself, love that God gives you from your birth.

00:30:58.136 --> 00:31:01.878
And then love for others.

00:31:03.840 --> 00:31:06.613
Which is actually the most important part of your life, your purpose .

00:31:06.613 --> 00:31:08.160
To spread love.

00:31:08.160 --> 00:31:12.640
Love for the God, animals, world, plants, etc.

00:31:12.640 --> 00:31:16.758
For family and friends of course.

00:31:16.758 --> 00:31:20.908
Love for everything that the God has given us.

00:31:24.880 --> 00:31:26.058
You can evangelize by spreading love.

00:31:28.040 --> 00:31:30.379
Thank you once again!

00:31:30.379 --> 00:31:33.360
Thank you to all of you that watch, comment and share this video.

00:31:33.360 --> 00:31:37.152
God bless all of you!

